        <h2>Crackhead Jack (2016, 2020)</h2>
        <p><i>The Adventures of Crackhead Jack</i> is a game I made with RPG Maker VXAce in 2016, released for free on <a href="https://gamejolt.com/games/the-adventures-of-crackhead-jack/148303">GameJolt</a>. You play as a man named Jack who is joined by two cultists to get back his crack that was taken by the police. It is a short and mechanically simple RPG filled with inside jokes and secret references, originally made as a <i>South Park</i>-esque parody of Vinesauce Joel's <i>BBQ Quest</i>. The <i>Cyanide & Happiness</i> style graphics are made by hand with a mouse and shitty used Wacom tablet in Paint.NET.</p> 
        <p>In 2020 it was <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1328500/">updated and re-released on Steam</a> as the <i>Overdose Edition</i>, featuring a gameplay balance overhaul and a story rewrite after I tried out drugs. It's $5, and also has <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1440820/The_Adventures_of_Crackhead_Jack_Overdose_Edition_Soundtrack/">an original soundtrack</a> thanks to some very talented friends &mdash; they get the soundtrack sales.</p>
